        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-06-24T05:59:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-06-24T05:59:00-05:00" n="230"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d230">
                <head>230. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">
                        <gloss target="#t_CIA1">CIA</gloss> Station</gloss> in [<hi rend="italic"
                        >place not declassified</hi>] to <gloss type="to">Operation <gloss
                            target="#t_PBSPBSUCCESS1">PBSUCCESS</gloss> Headquarters in
                        Florida</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d230fn1">Source: Central Intelligence Agency,
                        Job 79–010125A, Box 148, Folder 2. Secret; Routine; RYBAT; <gloss
                            target="#t_PBSPBSUCCESS1">PBSUCCESS</gloss>. Repeated to the Director of
                        Central Intelligence.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>[<hi rend="italic">place not declassified</hi>], <date
                        calendar="gregorian" when="1954-06-24T10:59:00+00:00">June 24, 1954,
                        1059Z</date>.</dateline>
                <p>1100. Re: <gloss target="#t_DIR1">DIR</gloss> 02987.<note n="2" xml:id="d230fn2"
                        >Not printed. (Ibid., Box 8, Folder 7)</note>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <persName>Osorio</persName> told Ambassador following 23 June: <list>
                        <label>A.</label>
                        <item>Does not trust ERRATIC and has never seen him although ERRATIC has
                            claimed <persName>Osorio</persName> support.</item>
                        <label>B.</label>
                        <item>ERRATIC attempted on several occasions to arrange interview with
                            him.</item>
                        <label>C.</label>
                        <item>
                            <persName>Osorio</persName> not supporting <persName corresp="#p_CJH1"
                                >Calligeris</persName>.</item>
                        <label>D.</label>
                        <item>
                            <persName corresp="#p_CJH1">Calligeris</persName> and ERRATIC
                            individually too ambitious and ERRATIC should throw in his support with
                                <persName corresp="#p_CJH1">Calligeris</persName>.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
